## Troubleshooting

**Macro doesn't appear when I type `/`**
The HTML or iframe macro may be disabled for your Confluence space. Ask your IT or Atlassian admin to enable it for the People Team space — it's a one-click setting in the Confluence admin panel.

**Dashboard loads but fonts look different**
GitHub Pages serves over HTTPS which allows Google Fonts to load. This is expected — it'll look right when embedded via the live URL.

**Dashboard looks cut off in Confluence**
Increase the iframe height. Try 1000 or 1100px. You can also add `scrolling="yes"` to the iframe tag to let people scroll inside it.

**I want to update the dashboard later**
Just go back to your GitHub repo, click the `index.html` file, click the pencil (Edit) icon, and paste in your new HTML. Or upload a new file to replace it. Changes go live within a minute.

